snippet.title: Mold review and faux amber tutorial
snippet.description:
This video is a review of molds I got from barsikmoy etsy shop. in the video I said these molds were from Russia, they are not. Those are other molds I'm waiting on to do a review of. I highly recommend these molds.     The only let down was the not glossy finish when I pulled the molds out but that was an easy fix. please visit my etsy page and like my Facebook and Instagram pages for more updates.
https://www.etsy.com/shop/ColesCrochetStore
https://www.facebook.com/colescrochetstore/
https://instagram.com/coles_crochet_and_woodcrafts?igshid=1a2t46j7oo90n




 The link for the molds are;
https://www.etsy.com/listing/662967626/silicon-mold-cabochons-irregular-shape
https://www.etsy.com/listing/676813375/silicon-mold-cabochons-irregular-shape

To get the high gloss shine I was looking for I used hutt ultra gloss finish. here is the link for that.
https://www.woodcraft.com/products/hut-ultra-gloss-plastic-polish

The resin I like to use is amazing clear cast resin by allumite. it's my favorite resin for doing things that will be dyed because it can get a little yellow with time. here is the link. 
https://amzn.to/2QPhAId
 
the dye I use for all of my coloring that isn't alcohol ink is this.
https://amzn.to/2Unw1W0

white alcohol ink
https://amzn.to/2xovD0K

The glitter i got from Ebay
https://www.ebay.com/itm/402023866264

heat gun
https://amzn.to/3dA108U

the UV resin I use 
https://amzn.to/3bygtVr

and the UV light
https://amzn.to/33PVlr9
